    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a legal arrangement where a third party holds and regulates payment of the funds required for two parties involved in a given transaction. In the context of buying a house, it ensures that your money is safe until all conditions of the sale are met, such as the home inspection, sale of your old house, and transferring the title. This prevents you and the seller from walking away from the deal without fulfilling your obligations. It's a way to protect both parties and make sure the transaction is completed smoothly.",
