    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow process is designed to minimize risks, but no system is entirely foolproof. However, reputable banks, escrow companies, and attorneys handle these accounts with strict regulations and oversight to ensure the funds are secure and properly managed. If a mistake occurs, it's typically due to human error, and the responsible party will usually rectify the issue promptly. If you have concerns, it's wise to choose a highly reputable escrow agent and to keep in close communication with your real estate professional to ensure everything is proceeding correctly. In rare cases, disputes might arise, but these are usually resolved through legal channels. Always have a clear understanding of the terms and conditions of the escrow agreement to protect your interests.",
